This paper discusses the challenges and solutions for achieving ultra-reliable and low-latency communications in vehicular networks, which are primarily related to networking and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses optimization frameworks for latency and reliability, which are related to information theory, leading to the possibility of cs.IT (Information Theory) being a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential challenges and solutions for establishing URLLC VNETs, which can be considered as a system-level problem, leading to the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) being a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the security challenges in VNETs, which can be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
